caption.text: Art will always have a story to tell, either through vivid strokes or solid hues, it's always something that can make anyone think of what it's meant to say. Just like the drawings and displays at the @damarkurungfestival , these drawings were meant to shed light and entertain the crowd with many stories to tell.

This Annual event is composed of keen and diligent locals to who want to preserve the endangered craft, Damar Kurung. Make sure to stay updated on events they will have by following their account: @damarkurungfestival .
.

Originating from Gresik Java, Indonesia, this lantern is an endangered craft that holds an interesting histroy in the Muslim culture in the form of art. It symbolizes the welcoming of the lailatul qodar in the month of Ramadan in the Islamic Calendar when people hang these lanterns in their houses. Each side of the lantern is decorated with drawings that signify happenings that take part during Ramadan. .

caption.text:
H-3 to our Charity Event: 
Save Tradition with Celebration 
On 18 July 2017 at RPTRA Menteng
.
.
The event's purpose is to spread awareness on the endangered Damar Kurung, an local Indonesian Craft that millenials lack knowledge of. It is inline with a Breakfasting event with children from RPTRA menteng who will be participating on workshops during the event as well. 
You can participate as well by leaving a comment below or sending us a DM! .
